        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 7:48AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 748 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Mosley, or 8 miles north of Danville, moving northeast
at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ranger...                         Lake Dardanelle State Park...
Lutherville...                    Long Pool Campground...
Piney Bay Recreation Area...      Pleasant Valley in Pope County...
Broomfield...                     Mt Nebo State Park...
Dabney...                         Solo...
Simpson...                        Spring Lake Campground...
Augsburg...                       Dover...
Lake Dardanelle...                Hector...
Nogo...                           Delaware...
Treat...                          Knoxville...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
